headline: Quanta Services (PWR) Valuation Check After Strong Year-to-Date Share Price Gains
summary: Quanta Services (PWR) has been quietly rewarding patient investors, with the stock up roughly 17% over the past 3 months and nearly 39% year to date, outpacing many industrial peers. See our latest analysis for Quanta Services. The latest pullback in Quanta’s 7 day share price return contrasts with its strong 90 day share price return and robust multi year total shareholder returns. This suggests momentum is cooling a touch rather than breaking. If Quanta’s run has you thinking about what...

headline: Does AEP’s US$72 Billion Grid Expansion And Data Center Focus Change The Bull Case For AEP?
summary: Earlier this month, American Electric Power Company raised its long-term EPS growth outlook to 7%–9% and expanded its five-year capital investment plan to US$72.00 billion, supported by long-term agreements with Quanta Services to build high-voltage transmission for rising data center-driven demand. This combination of a larger growth target, a significantly bigger grid buildout, and dedicated construction partners suggests AEP is repositioning itself as a core supplier of power...

headline: 3 Reasons We Love Quanta (PWR)
summary: Quanta currently trades at $436.93 and has been a dream stock for shareholders. It’s returned 535% since December 2020, blowing past the S&P 500’s 82.9% gain. The company has also beaten the index over the past six months as its stock price is up 21.8% thanks to its solid quarterly results.
